Such bureaucratic interference undermines individuals' rational self-interest to form and define their own private associations without state validation or oversight. This non-productive diversion of resources, funded by coercive taxation, shifts focus from genuine productive achievement to the construction of control mechanisms, stifling personal initiative and innovation by forcing private organizations to comply with arbitrary state demands. Ultimately, this replaces individual liberty and reasoned action with an irrational, expanding collectivist bureaucracy antithetical to a society founded on personal freedom and laissez-faire capitalism.
